A former governor of Kano State and the current senator representing Kano-South, Kabiru Gaya, has emerged the new the director-general of the Vice-President Yemi Osinbajo campaign, which is known as the The Progressive Project (TPP). This was disclosed on Thursday during a press conference in Abuja. Recall that the lawmaker was governor of Kano State from January 1992 – November 1993 and has been a senator since 2007. Gaya had also been a patron of the Osinbajo Volunteers Movement.